"Baldasanomanga J.M., Soriano C., Boada L.","Emission inventory for greenhouse gases in the City of Barcelona, 1987-1996",1999,"Atmospheric Environment","33","23",,"3765","3775",,,10.1016/S1352-2310(99)00086-2,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0033213749&partnerID=40&md5=c85d8916c0aaefe4335f7d8769350f51","Univ. Politecnica de Catalunya (UPC), Avd. Diagonal 647, planta 10, 08028 Barcelona, Spain; Ambit d'Urbanisme i Medi Ambient, Ajuntament de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain","Baldasanomanga, J.M., Univ. Politecnica de Catalunya (UPC), Avd. Diagonal 647, planta 10, 08028 Barcelona, Spain; Soriano, C., Univ. Politecnica de Catalunya (UPC), Avd. Diagonal 647, planta 10, 08028 Barcelona, Spain; Boada, L., Ambit d'Urbanisme i Medi Ambient, Ajuntament de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain","Emissions of greenhouse gases for the City of Barcelona are estimated for the period 1987-1994. The sources considered are: public and private transportation; industrial, commercial and domestic activities; and municipal solid waste disposal. The results show that the main source of CO2 emissions in Barcelona is private vehicle transportation, which accounts, as an average for the period studied, for 35% of total emissions. The second most important source is the municipal solid waste landfill facility of the city (24% of total emissions). The percentages for the remaining sources under consideration were: 14% electricity, 12% natural gas, 5% incineration, and 3% liquefied petroleum gases. However, the values for CO2 emissions per inhabitant over the period studied are lower than those for any other industrialized city available for comparison. This is closely related to the high percentage of electricity generation from nuclear power stations and hydro power facilities, and also to the extensive use of natural gas for domestic uses.","Emission inventories; Global warming; Greenhouse gases; Local scale studies","Emission inventory; Greenhouse gases; Air pollution; Carbon dioxide; Gas emissions; Greenhouse effect; Industrial emissions; Land fill; Mass transportation; Solid wastes; Atmospheric composition; carbon dioxide; liquefied petroleum gas; natural gas; atmospheric pollution; emission inventory; greenhouse gas; pollutant source; article; controlled study; greenhouse effect; household; incineration; industry; landfill; nuclear power plant; priority journal; solid waste management; Spain; traffic; urban area; Spain",,"carbon dioxide, 124-38-9, 58561-67-4; liquefied petroleum gas, 68476-85-7; natural gas, 8006-14-2",,,,"(1997) Anuari Estadístic de la Ciutat de Barcelona, , Ajuntament de Barcelona, Any 1996. Departament d'Estadística. Barcelona, (and previous years); Baldasano, J.M., (1996) Medidas para la Reducción en el Municipio de Barcelona de las Emisiones de los Gases Causantes del Incremento del Efecto Invernadero, , Ajuntament de Barcelona, informe ITEMA-AYBCN296/CO2; Baldasano, J.M., Guidelines and formulation of an upgrade source emission model for atmospheric pollutants (1998) Air Pollution Emissions Inventory. Advanced Series in Air Pollution, 3, pp. 1-49. , Baldasano, J.M., Power, H. (Eds.), Computational Mechanics Publication, Southampton; Baldasano, J.M., Fernández, J.C., (1998) Estimació de les Emissions de Gasos d'Efecte Hivernacle per a Catalunya, , Informe DMA1998/CO2. Departament de Medi Ambient, Generalitat de Catalunya; Bouscaren, R., Corinair inventory (1992) Default Emission Factors Handbook, Second Ed., , CEE; Costa, M., Baldasano, J.M., Development of a source emission model for atmospheric pollutants in the Barcelona area (1996) Atmospheric Environment, 30 A (2), pp. 309-318; (1991) The Changing Atmosphere: Strategies for Reducing CO2 Emissions, 2. , City of Toronto, Technical Volume. Special Advisory Committee on the Environment. Report Number Two-; (1995) Strategie di Riduzzione delle Emissioni di Anidride Carbonica, , Assesorato Ambiente e Territorio; (1992) Estadístiques Energètiques de Catalunya, , Departame